We have 110 charters attested by chaplains between 1045 and 1050. But after Ulf's appointment to Dorchester we are better informed. From 1053 to 1062 evidence about the chancery is to seek. But the outstanding chaplain of the period is the Lotharingian Giso. The little that we know of his life leads us to regard him as a man of affairs.
